description.originalText: Eka is the most wonderful caregiver. She takes excellent care of our infant, is respectful of our schedule/routine, on time and communicative and always engaging with our baby boy. Would highly recommend her!

description.displayText:
Eka is an absolutely wonderful caregiver. She has been providing part-time support for my 2 year old. 

She was able to quickly build rapport with him and whenever she is with him, she is very active and he is always happy and engaged - whether they are playing pretend games in the living room, cooking together (he helps mix), reading, or going to the park. She is very dependable and helpful, and is a pleasure to work with.

description.displayText: Eka is AMAZING! We hired her on a part-time basis to help look after our 2 month old son back in Dec 2021 and she has been with us ever since. She is reliable, punctual and has tremendous experience looking after infants and toddlers. Eka went above and beyond time after time when it came to taking of our son - exercises to encourage muscle development, taking care him out for long walks to get fresh air, play times in the park and in the playroom, etc. She is also an amazing cook and would spoil us with her Georgian delicacies as well as prepare meals for our son once he transitioned to solids. At this point, she is basically like family to us and our son. Every time she walks into our apartment in the morning, he can't stop containing his excitement. We are moving out-of-state, and sadly, can't take Eka with us. She will be missed. If you are looking an incredible, reliable, experienced nanny for your infant or toddler, we cannot recommend her enough.

description.displayText: Eka took care of my daughter from around 6 months till 2 years old until we moved away. She is INCREDIBLE! I highly recommend her to anyone looking for childcare. She is such a warm and lovely person who is such a pleasure to have in your home. She loved my daughter as if she was her own, which I cherished and it gave me a lot of comfort as a new mom. My daughter absolutely thrived under her care. She was very open to learning new things and I valued her experience as well. Eka is the best!

description.displayText: Eka was an amazing nanny for our family. She became a part of the family. Always dependable. She never called out sick or not showed up. She raised our infant son until he was 19 months and took care of Our infant daughter when she was born. She cooked and did light housekeeping as well. Wish we could have taken her with us when we moved from jersey city.

description.displayText: Eka had become part of our family in the last year while taking care of our son. She had been incredibly energetic and loving with him, she was very attentive to the details of how we want him to be fed and cared for and she was awesome at engaging with him and gaining his trust. He loved seeing her and spending time together. She cooked for him, they sang songs and read books together! Sadly, we moved and had to send our son to daycare, but Eka had been an amazing caregiver for him and I will cherish the help she gave our family!
